S7.title: 12 hour☘️ Study with me LIVE ☕ calm cozy ambience🩺POMODORO🔥Real-time study #Medgirl 2025-04-05 09:26
S7.description:
📩open me:

Hi!
Welcome to another Study with me
Thanks for joining
_________________________

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. Hopefully, this would get you motivated more for studying. You might hear the rain, birds, typing sounds and the flipping of pages (and cars too, unfortunately) from time to time, and I hope that helps you know that I'm there studying with you!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy. 
_____________________________

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡
_____________________________
💡Please adjust the volume for each of the background music that comes out.
The ASMR that comes out with 💡 is the sound of burning wood and Rain. 
_____________________________

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

💭Thoughts and purpose of this channel:

In today's world it's so difficult to congregate your focus for a particular work. There are distractions everywhere and it's too easy to lose your self-consciousness to these distractions. During this period of engrossment, It becomes essential for us to take back our consciousness and get out of the pool of distractions which seems pleasureful to swim in but is slowly submerging us into it. Best way to avoid these things is to be conscious and engage yourself in the activity which is actually important to you. It is the exact purpose of this channel. This channel is rooted onto the foundation of making progress and helping other to make progress. 

Personally, I get motivated by watching other people study. I've been watching these "study with me" sessions of other youtubers from long ago (until I started my own), and being honest, it helped me a lot. I am heartily thankful for those youtubers who helped me to make my study effective and I can confront that they created a positive impact in my life. Since I'm in their place right now, I can't be more happier than to be able to make the same positive impact on other people's life. There is a quotation saying "Helping others is the way we help ourselves". I feel that helping people and being able to make a positive impact in other people's life is the greatest thing a human can do. So, I think that you have understood the soul purpose of creating this channel.

S75.description:
🔴 ***Live Study With Me | (60 Min Study + 10 Min Rest) | Fireplace Ambience*** 🔥📚  

Welcome to this *Live Study With Me* session designed to help you stay focused, productive, and motivated! We’ll be following the **Pomodoro Technique** with **60 minutes of focused study** followed by **10 minutes of rest**.  

Enjoy the calming crackling sound of a fireplace in the background to create a cozy and aesthetic study atmosphere. Whether you’re preparing for exams, working on a project, or simply looking to stay productive, this session is perfect for you!  

### **Daily Routine**:  
📅 **Two Live Streams Every Day (IST)**:  
1. **Morning Stream**: Starts between **4:30 AM – 5:00 AM** and runs for **8 hours**.  
2. **Afternoon Stream**: Starts at **3:00 PM** and runs for **6 hours**, marking the end of the day.  

Join us daily and build a consistent study habit!  

### **How It Works**:  
⏳ **Pomodoro Schedule**:  
- 50 minutes of study  
- 10 minutes of rest  
(Repeated throughout the session)  

🔥 **Background Ambience**:  
- Relaxing fireplace crackling sound for a warm and comforting environment.  
- Music: https://www.chosic.com/free-music/all/ 

💡 **Tips for a Productive Session**:  
1. Prepare your study materials before starting.  
2. Stay hydrated and keep a snack nearby for breaks.  
3. Minimize distractions and immerse yourself in the session.  

### **Stream Rules**:  
🚨 **Be Respectful**:  
- Keep the chat positive and encouraging for everyone.  

📵 **No Spamming**:  
- Avoid excessive messages, emojis, or off-topic comments.  

🌐 **Stay On-Topic**:  
- Chat should focus on study-related topics or productivity.  

❤️ **Encourage Others**:  
- Support fellow viewers in staying focused and motivated.  

⚠️ **No Self-Promotion**:  
- Please avoid advertising or promoting other channels, services, or products.  

### **Let’s achieve your goals together!**  
If you enjoy this session, don’t forget to **like, comment, and subscribe** for more study content.
